verbs.description: undust (third-person singular simple present undusts, present participle undusting, simple past and past participle undusted)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To free from dust; remove dust from
examples: It took the state accountants awhile to undust [cq] and figure out his travel expense claims. They would include maybe a pound of coffee, a dozen eggs, a package of cereal, etc. No hotel bills.
